itterFix","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Controls how much physics ticks are synchronized with real time. For 0 or less, the ticks are synchronized. Such values are recommended for network games, where clock synchronization matters. Higher values cause higher deviation of the in-game clock and real clock but smooth out framerate jitters. The default value of 0.5 should be fine for most; values above 2 could cause the game to react to dropped frames with a noticeable delay and are not recommended."}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Engine/physicsJitterFix":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Controls how much physics ticks are synchronized with real time. For 0 or less, the ticks are synchronized. Such values are recommended for network games, where clock synchronization matters. Higher values cause higher deviation of the in-game clock and real clock but smooth out framerate jitters. The default value of 0.5 should be fine for most; values above 2 could cause the game to react to dropped frames with a noticeable delay and are not recommended."}],"title":"physicsJitterFix","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/engine\/physicsjitterfix","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Engine\/physicsJitterFix","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"physicsJitterFix","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"title":"SwiftGodot","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","abstract":[{"text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/E